  "prompt": "What is the best way to learn spoken English?",
  "response": "Here are some effective ways to learn spoken English:\n\n1. Immersion techniques\n- Watch English movies, TV shows, and YouTube videos\n- Listen to English podcasts and music\n- Practice speaking with native speakers\n\n2. Language learning methods\n- Take conversation classes\n- Use language exchange apps like Tandem or HelloTalk\n- Attend English speaking clubs\n\n3. Daily practice strategies\n- Think in English\n- Talk to yourself in English\n- Practice pronunciation with online resources\n- Record and listen to yourself speaking\n\n4. Interactive learning\n- Use language learning apps like Duolingo or Babbel\n- Join online language learning communities\n- Participate in English conversation groups\n\n5. Practical approaches\n- Start conversations with English speakers\n- Don't be afraid of making mistakes\n- Focus on communication, not perfection\n- Learn informal/conversational English\n\n6. Structured learning\n- Take English classes\n- Work with a private tutor\n- Follow structured online courses\n\n7. Supplementary techniques\n- Read English books aloud\n- Use language learning websites\n- Learn idiomatic expressions\n- Study pronunciation and intonation\n\nConsistency and regular practice are key to improving spoken English skills.",
